现在我有atomic_image_questions.jsonl            mechanics_image_questions.jsonl  quantum_vol1_image_questions.jsonl  solid_state_image_questions.jsonl
electromagnetism_image_questions.jsonl  optics_image_questions.jsonl     quantum_vol2_image_questions.jsonl  thermo_image_questions.jsonl这些jsonl文件，其中的数据的格式为：{"source_index": 0, "sub_id": 1, "multimodal": true, "image": "atomic_0116/_page_31_Figure_9.jpeg", "question": "<image>Explain the principle of using backscattering techniques to analyze the composition of solid materials. (As shown in the figure: a monoenergetic ion beam strikes the sample and undergoes elastic collisions with target nuclei; the energy \\(E'\\) of the scattered ions is detected at the scattering angle \\(\\theta\\).)", "answer": "When the incident energy is below the threshold for nuclear reactions with the target nuclei, the incident ions undergo elastic collisions with the target nuclei (as shown in the figure). Let the incident particle have mass \\(m_1\\) and energy \\(E_0\\), and the target atom have mass \\(m_2\\). The ion energy received at the scattering angle \\(\\theta\\) is\n\\[\nE' = K^2 E_0,\\quad \nK=\\frac{m_1\\cos\\theta+\\sqrt{m_2^2-m_1^2\\sin^2\\theta}}{m_1+m_2}.\n\\]\nUnder fixed experimental conditions, \\(E'\\) depends only on \\(m_2\\); therefore, the target element (or impurity) species can be identified from the peak position in the backscattering energy spectrum. The peak area is proportional to the content of that element and to the Rutherford scattering cross section at that angle, thereby determining the relative abundance. For thin targets, energy loss can be neglected and the above relation applied directly; for thick targets, ionization energy loss must be considered, and the backscattered ion energy depends on the collision depth, so depth-distribution information of the elements can be obtained.", "question_ch": "<image>1.7 试说明用背散射技术分析固体材料组分的原理。（如图 1.1 所示：单能离子束打到样品上，与靶核发生弹性碰撞，在散射角 θ 处探测到散射离子能量 E′）", "answer_ch": "在入射能量低于与靶核发生核反应阈值时，入射离子与靶核发生弹性碰撞（图 1.1）。设入射粒子质量为 \\(m_1\\)、能量为 \\(E_0\\)，靶原子质量为 \\(m_2\\)，在散射角 \\(\\theta\\) 处接收到的离子能量为\n\\[\nE' = K^2 E_0,\\quad \nK=\\frac{m_1\\cos\\theta+\\sqrt{m_2^2-m_1^2\\sin^2\\theta}}{m_1+m_2}.\n\\]\n在确定实验条件下 \\(E'\\) 只与 \\(m_2\\) 有关，因此由背散射能谱峰位置可确定靶元素（或杂质）种类；而峰面积正比于该元素含量及该角度的卢瑟福散射截面，从而确定相对丰度。薄靶可忽略能量损失直接应用上述关系；厚靶需考虑电离能损，背散射离子能量与碰撞深度相关，因此可得到元素的深度分布信息。", "book_name": "atomic", "relevant_section_id_0": "1", "relevant_section_id_1": "7", "relevant_section_id_2": "12", "llm_raw_response": "{\"book_name\":\"atomic\",\"relevant_section_id_0\":\"1\",\"relevant_section_id_1\":\"7\",\"relevant_section_id_2\":\"12\"}", "context": ["Atomic_physics/page_16.png", "Atomic_physics/page_17.png", "Atomic_physics/page_18.png", "Atomic_physics/page_19.png", "Atomic_physics/page_20.png", "Atomic_physics/page_21.png", "Atomic_physics/page_22.png", "Atomic_physics/page_23.png", "Atomic_physics/page_24.png", "Atomic_physics/page_25.png", "Atomic_physics/page_26.png", "Atomic_physics/page_27.png", "Atomic_physics/page_28.png", "Atomic_physics/page_29.png", "Atomic_physics/page_30.png", "Atomic_physics/page_31.png", "Atomic_physics/page_32.png", "Atomic_physics/page_33.png", "Atomic_physics/page_34.png", "Atomic_physics/page_35.png", "Atomic_physics/page_36.png"]}，我希望从每个数据集中随机提取100条数据出来作为测试集合，剩下的作为训练集合，然后保存为data = {
            "data_source": "poem",
"prompt": [{"role": "user", "content": query}],
"context": book_paths,
"ability": "long_memory_physics",
"reward_model": {
"style": "rule",
"ground_truth": answer,
            },
"extra_info": {
"index": idx,
"num_pages": num_pages,
"ability": "long_memory_physics",
"prompt": [{"role": "user", "content": query}],
"need_tools_kwargs": False,
            },
        }这种格式的数据，并且保存一份jsonl文件和一份parquet文件。注意在提取数据时，quantum_vol1_image_questions.jsonl和quantum_vol2_image_questions.jsonl是一类数据，所以应该先将其合并然后随机取100条即可。
